    parse_example(example_proto)[source]¶

    Parses one example from a TFRecord data.

    1. Set the parsing configuration according to the format in which the data was written. (tf.io.parse_single_example())

    2. When writing TFRecord data, we make the elements one-dimensional, so we restore the shape.

    3. Run preprocess. (preprocess())

    Parameters:

    example_proto (tf.Tensor) – protocol massage.

    Returns:

    • tf.Tensor – input.

    • tf.Tensor – label.

    make_loader_example(seed=0)[source]¶

    Makes data loader.

    1. Set the list of data file pathes. (tf.data.Dataset.list_files())

    2. Set the interleave configuration. (tf.data.Dataset.interleave())

    3. Set the function to parse one example from a TFRecord data. (tf.data.Dataset.map())

    4. Set the shuffle configuration. (tf.data.Dataset.shuffle())

    5. Set the batch configuration. (tf.data.Dataset.batch())

    6. Set the prefetch configuration. (tf.data.Dataset.prefetch())

    7. Set the repeat configuration. (tf.data.Dataset.repeat())

    Parameters:

    seed (int) – random seed.

    Returns:

    Callable – data pipeline. (tf.data)

    feature_int64_list(value)[source]¶

    Converts tf.train.Feature type. (tf.train.Int64List)

    Parameters:

    value (list[int]) – one-dimensional list with elements of type int.

    Returns:

    tf.train.Feature – value of tf.train.Feature type.

    value = [1,2,3]
print(feature_int64_list(value=value))

# int64_list {
# value: 1
# value: 2
# value: 3
# }

    class Processor(params)[source]¶

    Bases: object

    Processes data.

    • Used to process data when making a tf.data data pipeline.

    • If you want to use some other settings, implement it as a method of this class. If you implemented, set the name as the func key in __init__() and the method as the value.

    Parameters:

    params (dict[str, Any]) – parameters.
